  "title": "In-house Interior Designer",
  "description": "<p>Prepare detailed design proposals, including technical and 3D drawings.</p><p>Select and source furniture, fixtures, and finishes to enhance design concepts.</p><p>Develop creative, innovative, and functional interior design concepts and plans.</p><p>Source and request for quotations from contractors to ensure price competitiveness.</p><p>Manage the delivery of the project and budgets accordingly.</p><p>Utilize industry best practice, techniques, and standards throughout the project execution.</p><p>Manage fitting out projects ensuring adherence to quality standards.<br /></p><h2><strong>Requirements:</strong></h2><p>Diploma/Degree in Interior Design or a related field.</p><p>Minimum 1 year interior design experience or fit out experience in retail/commercial projects.</p><p>Proficient in AutoCAD (knowledge of other design software is a plus).</p><p>Strong attention to detail and ability to meet tight deadlines.</p><p>Good communication and teamwork skills.</p><p>Responsible, self-motivated, proactive and independent at work.</p><p>Must be able to perform night work on weekends / Public Holiday when projects are ongoing. </p><p><br />\n\n</p>",
